definition.value: A 3-penten-1-yne in which the double bond adopts a cis-configuration.
Any acetylenic compound containing five carbon-carbon triple bonds.
Any insecticide that is capable of killing egg cells.
An octene that is octane containing one double bond at position 3.
A 2-enoyl-CoA in which the double bond between positions 2 and 3 of the S-acyl group has cis- geometry; major microspecies at pH 7.3
An octene that is octane containing one double bond at position 2.
An amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of pantothenic acid and the amino group of cysteamine.
A 5-oxo-2-furylacetic acid having a 3-methyl substituent.
A hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 8-hydroxylauric acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 10-hydroxylauric acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 9-hydroxylauric acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 9-hydroxymyristic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 10-hydroxymyristic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 12-hydroxymyristic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 11-hydroxymyristic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A sesterterpenoid that is ophiobolane with a hydroxy group at position 3, oxo group at positions 5, formyl group at position 7, and double bonds at positions 7-8 and 19-20.

A member of the class of resorcinols that is 5-heptadecylbenzene-1,3-diol which carries cis double bonds at positions 2 and 6, trans double bonds at positions 4 and 15, and a methyl group at position 15.
A dihydroxy-5beta-cholanic acid that is (5beta)-cholan-24-oic acid substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 3 and 7 respectively.
An alkene that is dodecane containing one double bond at unspecified position.
A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of soppiline C, arising from the deprotonation of the carboxy group. Major species at pH 7.3.
A dodecene that is dodecane with a double bond at position 3.
A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of cannabichromenic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group. Major species at pH 7.3.
A dodecene that is dodecane with a double bond at position 2.
A 2-dodecene that is dodecane which has been dehydrogenated to introduce a cis double bond between positions 2 and 3.
A chromenol that is 2H-chromene substituted by methyl, 2-methylpent-2-en-5-yl, hydroxy, carboxy and pentyl groups at positions 2,2,5,6 and 7, respectively.
A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of soppiline A, arising from the deprotonation of the carboxy group. Major species at pH 7.3.

Any oligosaccharide, polysaccharide or their derivatives consisting of monosaccharides or monosaccharide derivatives linked by glycosidic bonds. See also http://www.ontobee.org/ontology/GNO?iri=http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GNO_00000001.

A branched amino oligosaccharide that is an octadecasaccharide comprising a linear trisaccharide of beta-D-mannose and two N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues all linked in sequence (1->4), to the mannosyl residue of which are linked an N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl residue [via a (1->4) linkage], an N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl-(2->6)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-[N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl-(2->6)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->6)]-alpha-D-mannosyl branched heptasaccharide unit [linked (1->6)], and an an N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl-(2->6)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-[N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl-(2->6)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)]-alpha-D-mannosyl branched heptasaccharide unit [linked (1->3)].

A pyrrolopurine that is saxitoxin carrying a hydroxy substituent on the nitrogen atom at position 5. It is a sodium channel blocker that is undergoing clinical trials as a prolonged-duration local anesthetic.

A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid that is icosanoic acid carrying a hydroxy group at position 3R, methyl group at position 18, cis double bonds at positions 5 and 9, and trans double bonds at positions 7 and 18.

A member of the class of resorcinols that is 16-(3,5-dihydroxyphenyl)hexadecanoic acid which carries cis double bonds at positions 10 and 14, a trans double bond at position 12, and an ethylidene group at position 2.
An alkaloid compound that is 2,6-diamino-4-methyl-pyrollo[1,2-c]-purin-10-diol produced by several cyanobacteria and dinoflagellates, which can result in paralytic shellfish poisoning when ingested.

A branched amino oligosaccharide that is a hexadecasaccharide derivative comprising a linear tetrasaccharide of beta-D-mannose and three N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues all linked in sequence (1->4), to the N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues at the reduciong end and the one proximal to it are each linked (1->6) L-fucosyl residues, while to the beta-D-mannose residue of which are linked two N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-[alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->3)]-[alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)]-alpha-D-mannosyl branched pentasaccharide units via (1->3) and (1->6) linkages.
An indole alkaloid with formula C22H21N3O3S. It is a natural product synthesized by an NRPS/PKS system in Streptomyces sp. B917 and exhibits antifungal properties.
A hydroxy fatty acid comprising lauric acid carrying a single hydroxy substituent at position 8.
A hydroxy fatty acid comprising lauric acid carrying a single hydroxy substituent at position 9.
